   "description": "Lars Fredrik Kemner is a Swedish artist known for his landscape paintings of the plains around Uppsala and the West Coast (Bohuslän). He was born on October 4, 1919, in Uppsala. Lars Fredrik Kemner married Anna Grettve, a school kitchen teacher, in 1945. He studied at the Art Academy from 1937 to 1942. Lars Fredrik Kemner exhibited his works at the Uppland exhibition in Uppsala and Gävle, as well as in Eskilstuna. He also had a solo exhibition in Uppsala in 1944."
